obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24740)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24740&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Energy Conservation`
  line `Act, 2001.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 28th June, 2012 (sections 31, 33, 44, 45), vide notification No. S. O. 1433(E), dated 28th June, 2012, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24741)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24741&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) accredited energy auditor means ^1[an energy auditor accredited in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of] clause (p) of sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(b) Appellate Tribunal means the Appellate Tribunal for Energy Conservation ^2[referred to in section 30];`
  line
  line `^3[^4 [(c) "building"means any structure or erection or part of structure or erection--`
  line
  line `(i) constructed after the rules relating to energy conservation and sustainable building codes have been notified by the Central Government under clause (p) of section 14 and by the State Government under clause (a) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(ii) which has a minimum connected load of 100 Kilowatt (kW) or contract demand of 120 Kilovolt Ampere (kVA); and`
  line
  line `(iii) which is used or intended to be used for commercial purpose or as an office building or for residential purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may specify a lower connected load or contract demand than the load or demand specified above;]`
  line
  line `(d) Bureau means the Bureau of Energy Efficiency established under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `^5 [(da) "carbon credit certificate" means the certificate issued by the Central Government or any agency authorised by it under section 14AA;`
  line
  line `(db) "carbon credit trading scheme" means the scheme for reduction of carbon emissions notified by the Central Government under clause (w) of section 14;]`
  line
  line `(e) Chairperson means the Chairperson of the Governing Council;`
  line
  line `(f) designated agency means any agency designated under clause (d) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(g) designated consumer means any consumer specified under clause (e) of section 14;`
  line
  line `^6 [ (h) "energy" means any form of energy derived from fossil fuels or non-fossil sources or renewable sources; ]`
  line
  line `(i) energy audit means the verification, monitoring and analysis of use of energy including`
  line `submission of technical report containing recommendations for improving energy efficiency with`
  line `cost benefit analysis and an action plan to reduce energy consumption;`
  line
  line `^7 [(ia) "energy auditor" means any individual possessing the qualifications prescribed under clause (m) of section 14; ]`
  line
  line `^8[(j) "energy conservation and sustainable building code" means the code which provides norms and standards for energy efficiency and its conservation, use of renewable energy and other green building requirements for a building;];`
  line
  line `(k) energy consumption standards means the norms for process and energy consumption`
  line `standards specified under clause (a) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(l) Energy Management Centre means the Energy Management Centre set up under the`
  line `Resolution of the Government of India in the erstwhile Ministry of Energy, Department of Power No.`
  line `7(2)/87- EP(Vol. IV), dated the 5th July, 1989 and registered under the Societies Registration Act,`
  line `1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(m) energy manager means any individual possessing the qualifications prescribed under`
  line `clause (m) of section 14;`
  line
  line `^9[(ma) energy savings certificate means any energy savings certificate issued to the designated`
  line `consumers under sub-section (1) of section 14A;`
  line
  line `(maa) equipment or appliance means any equipment or appliance which consumes, generates,`
  line `transmits or supplies energy and includes any device that consumes any form of energy and produces`
  line `a desired work;]`
  line
  line `(n) Governing Council means the Governing Council referred to in section 4;`
  line
  line `(o) member means the member of the Governing Council and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(p) notification means a notification in the Gazette of India or, as the case may be, the Official`
  line `Gazette of a State;`
  line
  line `(q) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^10 [ (qa) "registered entity" means any entity, including designated consumers, registered for carbon credit trading scheme specified under clause (w) of section 14; ]`
  line
  line `(r) regulations means regulations made by the Bureau under this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) Schedule means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) State Commission means the State Electricity Regulatory Commission established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 17 of the Electricity Regulatory Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998);`
  line
  line `^11 [ (ta) "vehicle" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (28) of section 2 of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988);`
  line
  line `(tb) "vessel" includes every description of water craft used or capable of being used in inland waters or in coastal waters, including any ship, boat, sailing vessel, tug, barge or other description of vessel including non-displacement craft, amphibious craft, wing-in-ground craft, ferry, roll-on-roll-off vessel, container vessel, tanker vessel, gas carrier or floating unit or dumb vessel used for transportation, storage or accommodation within or through inland waters and coastal waters; ].`
  line
  line `(u) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Indian Electricity`
  line `Act, 1910 (9 of 1910) or the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948 (54 of 1948) or the Electricity Regulatory`
  line `Commissions Act, 1998 (14 of 1998) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in those`
  line Acts.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2010 s. 2, for "an auditor possessing qualifications specified under" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "established under section 30" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 2, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid. for clause (h) (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (j) (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 2, (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24742)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Bureau of Energy Efficiency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24742&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such`
  line `date as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established, for the purposes`
  line `of this Act, a Bureau to be called the Bureau of Energy Efficiency.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Bureau shall be at Delhi.`
  line
  line `(4) The Bureau may establish offices at other places in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24743)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Management of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24743&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the Bureau shall vest in the Governing Council which shall consist of not less than ^1[thirty-one, but not exceeding thirty-seven], members to be appointed by the Central Government..`
  line
  line `(2) The Governing Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in charge of the Ministry or Department`
  line `of the Central Government dealing with the Power`
  line `ex officio Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with the Power`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with the Petroleum and Natural Gas`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(d) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with the Coal`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(e) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with the Non-conventional Energy Sources`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(f) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with the Atomic Energy`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(g) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government`
  line `dealing with the Consumer Affairs`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `^2 [ (ga) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with the Environment, Forest and Climate Changeex officio member;`
  line
  line `(gb) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with the Housing and Urban Affairsex officio member;`
  line
  line `(gc) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with the Road Transport and Highwaysex officio member;`
  line
  line `(gd) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with the Steelex officio member;`
  line
  line `(ge) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with the Civil Aviationex officio member;`
  line
  line `(gf) the Secretary to the Government of India, in charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with the Ports, Shipping and Waterwaysex officio member;`
  line
  line `(gg) Member of the Railway Board (in charge of Energy), Ministry of Railwaysex officio member; ]`
  line
  line `(h) Chairman of the Central Electricity Authority established under the Electricity (Supply) Act, 1948`
  line `(54 of 1948)`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(i) Director-General of the Central Power Research`
  line `Institute registered under the Karnataka Societies Act,`
  line `1960 (Karnataka Act 17 of 1960)`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(j) Executive Director of the Petroleum Conservation`
  line `Research Association, a society registered under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (XXI of 1860)`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(k) Chairman-cum-Managing Director of the Central Mine`
  line `Planning and Design Institute Limited, a company`
  line `incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956)`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(l) Director-General of the Bureau of Indian Standards`
  line `established under the Bureau of Indian Standards Act,`
  line `1986 (63 of 1986)`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `(m) Director-General of the National Test House,`
  line `Department of Supply, Ministry of Commerce and`
  line `Industry, Kolkata`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `^3 [(ma) Director-General of the National Productivity Council, Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade, Ministry of Commerce and Industryex officio member;[`
  line
  line `(n) Managing Director of the Indian Renewable Energy`
  line `Development Agency Limited, a company`
  line `incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956)`
  line `ex officio member;`
  line
  line `^4[(o) one official each from the energy or power department of the five States from the five power regions, not below the rank of Principal Secretary to the State Government, to be appointed by the Central Governmentmember; ]`
  line
  line `^5[(p) such number of persons, not exceeding seven, as may be prescribed, to be appointed by the Central Government as members, from amongst persons who, in the opinion of the Central Government, are experts or capable of representing industry, equipment and appliance manufacturers, architects, institutes and consumersmember; ]`
  line
  line `(q) such number of persons, not exceeding two as may be`
  line `nominated by the Governing Council as members`
  line member;
  line
  line `(r) Director-General of Bureau ex officio member-secretary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Governing Council may exercise all powers and do all acts and things which may be`
  line `exercised or done by the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(4) Every member referred to in clauses (o), (p) and (q) of sub-section (2) shall hold office for a term`
  line `of three years from the date on which he enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(5) The fee and allowances to be paid to the members referred to in clauses (o), (p) and (q) of`
  line `sub-section (2) and the manner of filling up of vacancies and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 3, for twenty, but not exceeding twenty-six (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 3, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (o) (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (p) (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24744)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Meetings of Governing Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24744&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Council shall meet at such times and`
  line `places, and shall observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings`
  line `(including quorum at such meetings) as may be provided by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or, if for any reason, he is unable to attend a meeting of the Governing Council,`
  line `any other member chosen by the members present from amongst themselves at the meeting shall preside`
  line `at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Governing Council shall be decided by a`
  line `majority vote of the members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairperson`
  line `or in his absence, the person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24745)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Bureau, Governing Council or Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24745&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Bureau or the Governing Council or any Committee shall be invalid merely`
  line `by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Bureau or the Governing Council or`
  line `the Committee; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Director-General or Secretary of the`
  line `Bureau or a member of the Governing Council or the Committee; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Bureau or the Governing Council or the Committee not`
  line `affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24746)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal of member from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24746&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall remove a member referred to`
  line `in clauses (o), (p) and (q) of sub-section (2) of section 4 from office if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudicated as insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves a moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(d) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused his position as to render his`
  line `continuation in office detrimental to the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member shall be removed under this clause unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24747)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Constitution of Advisory Committees and other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24747&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any regulations`
  line `made in this behalf, the Bureau shall, within six months from the date of commencement of this Act,`
  line `constitute Advisory Committees for the efficient discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Advisory Committee shall consist of a Chairperson and such other members as may be`
  line `determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the powers contained in sub-section (1), the Bureau may constitute, such`
  line `number of technical committees of experts for the formulation of energy consumption standards or norms`
  line `in respect of equipment or processes, as it considers necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24748)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Director General of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 28 of 2010 s. 3, for "three years" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24748&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint a`
  line `Director-General from amongst persons of ability and standing, having adequate knowledge and`
  line `experience in dealing with the matters relating to energy production, supply and energy management,`
  line `standardisation and efficient use of energy and its conservation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint any person not below the rank of Deputy`
  line `Secretary to the Government of India as Secretary of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director-General shall hold office for a term of ^1[five years] from the date on which he enters`
  line `upon his office or until he attains the age of sixty years, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(4) The salary and allowances payable to the Director-General and other terms and conditions of his`
  line `service and other terms and conditions of service of the Secretary of the Bureau shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(5) Subject to general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs by the Governing`
  line `Council, the Director-General of the Bureau shall be the Chief Executive Authority of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(6) The Director-General of the Bureau shall exercise and discharge such powers and duties of the`
  line `Bureau as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24749)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers and employees of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "The Central Government" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24749&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[The Bureau] may appoint such other officers and`
  line `employees in the Bureau as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Bureau appointed`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24750)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Authentication of orders and decisions of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24750&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the Bureau`
  line `shall be authenticated by the signature of the Director-General or any other officer of the Bureau`
  line `authorised by the Director-General in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24751)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Transfer of assets, liabilities and employees of Energy Management Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24751&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and`
  line `from the date of establishment of the Bureau--`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the Energy Management Centre in any law other than this Act or in any`
  line `contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(b) all properties and assets, movable and immovable of, or belonging to, the Energy`
  line `Management Centre shall vest in the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(c) all the rights and liabilities of the Energy Management Centre shall be transferred to, and be`
  line `the rights and liabilities of, the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(d) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (c), all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred,`
  line `all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the Energy`
  line `Management Centre immediately before that date, for or in connection with the purposes of the said`
  line `Centre shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into, or engaged to be done by, with or for, the`
  line Bureau;
  line
  line `(e) all sums of money due to the Energy Management Centre immediately before that date shall`
  line `be deemed to be due to the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(f) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against the Energy Management Centre immediately before that date may be continued or may be`
  line `instituted by or against the Bureau; and`
  line
  line `(g) every employee holding any office under the Energy Management Centre immediately before`
  line `that date shall hold his office in the Bureau by the same tenure and upon the same terms and`
  line `conditions of service as respects remuneration, leave, provident fund, retirement or other terminal`
  line `benefits as he would have held such office if the Bureau had not been established and shall continue`
  line `to do so as an employee of the Bureau or until the expiry of six months from that date if such`
  line `employee opts not to be the employee of the Bureau within such period.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947) or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the absorption of any employee by the Bureau in its regular service`
  line `under this section shall not entitle such employee to any compensation under that Act or other law and no`
  line `such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24752)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Powers and functions of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24752&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau shall, effectively co-ordinate with designated`
  line `consumers, designated agencies and other agencies, recognise and utilise the existing resources and`
  line `infrastructure, in performing the functions assigned to it by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau may perform such functions and exercise such powers as may be assigned to it by or`
  line `under this Act and in particular, such functions and powers include the function and power to--`
  line
  line `(a) recommend to the Central Government the norms for processes and energy consumption`
  line `standards required to be notified under clause (a) of section 14;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) recommend to the Central Government for issuing of the energy savings certificate under`
  line `section 14A;]`
  line
  line `(b) recommend to the Central Government the particulars required to be displayed on label on`
  line `equipment or on appliances and manner of their display under clause (d) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) recommend to the Central Government for notifying any user or class of users of energy as a`
  line `designated consumer under clause (e) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(d) take suitable steps to prescribe guidelines for energy conservation building codes under clause`
  line `(p) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(e) take all measures necessary to create awareness and disseminate information for efficient use`
  line `of energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(f) arrange and organise training of personnel and specialists in the techniques for efficient use of`
  line `energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(g) strengthen consultancy services in the field of energy conservation;`
  line
  line `(h) promote research and development in the field of energy conservation;`
  line
  line `(i) develop testing and certification procedure and promote testing facilities for certification and`
  line `testing for energy consumption of equipment and appliances;`
  line
  line `(j) formulate and facilitate implementation of pilot projects and demonstration projects for`
  line `promotion of efficient use of energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(k) promote use of energy efficient processes, equipment, devices and systems;`
  line
  line `(l) promote innovative financing of energy efficiency projects;`
  line
  line `(m) give financial assistance to institutions for promoting efficient use of energy and its`
  line conservation;
  line
  line `(n) levy fee, as may be determined by regulations, for services provided for promoting efficient`
  line `use of energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(o) maintain a list of accredited energy auditors as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `^2[(p) specify, by regulations, the qualifications, criteria and conditions subject to which a person`
  line `may be accredited as an energy auditor and the procedure for such accreditation;]`
  line
  line `(q) specify, by regulations, the manner and intervals of time in which the energy audit shall be`
  line conducted;
  line
  line `(r) specify, by regulations, certification procedures for ^3[energy auditors and energy managers] to`
  line `be designated or appointed by designated consumers;`
  line
  line `(s) prepare educational curriculum on efficient use of energy and its conservation for educational`
  line `institutions, boards, universities or autonomous bodies and coordinate with them for inclusion of such`
  line `curriculum in their syllabus;`
  line
  line `^1[(sa) conduct examination for capacity building and strengthening of services in the field of`
  line `energy conservation including certification of energy managers and energy auditors;]`
  line
  line `(t) implement international co-operation programmes relating to efficient use of energy and its`
  line `conservation as may be assigned to it by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(u) perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act of 28 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (p) (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "energy managers" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (72536)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 14
  title `Prohibition of use of deceptive name, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=72536&sectionno=13A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Prohibition of use of deceptive name, etc.—(1) No person shall, without previous`
  line `permission of the Bureau, use any name which so nearly resembles the name of the Bureau as to deceive`
  line `or likely to deceive the public.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no registering`
  line `authority shall register any company, firm or other body of persons which bears any name or mark`
  line `resembling the name of the Bureau.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24753)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Central Government to enforce efficient use of energy and its conservation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24753&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, by notification, in consultation with the Bureau,--`
  line
  line `(a) specify the norms for processes and energy consumption standards for any equipment, ^1 [appliance, vehicle, vessel, industrial unit, building or establishment which consumes, generates, transmits or supplies energy; ]`
  line
  line `(b) specify equipment or appliance ^2 [or vehicle, vessel, industrial unit, building or establishment ] or class of equipments or appliances, as the case may be, for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(c) prohibit manufacture or import of any equipment or appliance or vehicle or vessel specified under clause (b), unless it conforms to energy consumption standards specified under clause (a):`
  line
  line `Provided that an industrial unit specified under clause (b) shall close its operations unless it conforms to the norms for processes or energy consumption standards specified under clause (a):`
  line
  line `Provided further that from the date of notification of norms for processes and energy consumption standards under clause (a), no notification prohibiting such manufacture or import shall be issued––`
  line
  line `(i) within a period of six months in the case of equipment or appliance or vehicle or vessel; and`
  line
  line `(ii) within a period of two years for closure of industrial unit:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Central Government may, having regard to the market share and the technological development having impact on equipment or appliance or vehicle or vessel, and for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the said period of six months referred to above, by a further period not exceeding six month;]`
  line
  line `(d) direct display of such particulars on label on equipment or on appliance specified under`
  line `clause (b) and in such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(e) specify, having regard to the intensity or quantity of energy consumed and the amount of`
  line `investment required for switching over to energy efficient equipments and capacity of industry to`
  line `invest in it and availability of the energy efficient machinery and equipment required by the industry,`
  line `^4[any user or class of users of energy in the energy intensive industries and other establishments as specified in the Schedule as a designated consumer] for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) alter the list of Energy Intensive Industries ^5[and other establishments ] specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(g) establish and prescribe such energy consumption norms and standards for designated`
  line `consumers as it may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may prescribe different norms and standards for different`
  line `designated consumers having regard to such factors as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(h) direct, having regard to quantity of energy consumed or the norms and standards of energy consumption specified under clause (a), the Energy Intensive Industries ^6and other establishments] specified in the Schedule to get energy audit conducted by an accredited energy auditor in such manner and intervals of time as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(i) direct, if considered necessary for efficient use of energy and its conservation, any designated`
  line `consumer to get energy audit conducted by an accredited energy auditor;`
  line
  line `(j) specify the matters to be included for the purposes of inspection under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(k) direct any designated consumer to furnish to the designated agency, in such form and manner`
  line `and within such period, as may be prescribed, the information with regard to the energy consumed`
  line `and action taken on the recommendation of the accredited energy auditor;`
  line
  line `(l) direct any designated consumer to designate or appoint ^7[energy auditor or energy manager ] in charge of activities for efficient use of energy and its conservation and submit a report, in the form and manner as may be prescribed, on the status of energy consumption at the end of every financial year to the designated agency;`
  line
  line `(m) prescribe minimum qualification for ^8[energy auditors and energy managers] to be designated`
  line `or appointed under clause (l);`
  line
  line `(n) direct every designated consumer to comply with energy consumption norms and standards;`
  line
  line `(o) direct any designated consumer, who does not fulfil the energy consumption norms and`
  line `standards prescribed under clause (g), to prepare a scheme for efficient use of energy and its`
  line `conservation and implement such scheme keeping in view the economic viability of the investment in`
  line `^9[such form, the time within which and the manner] as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(p) prescribe ^9[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] for efficient use of energy and its conservation in the building or building complex;`
  line
  line `(q) amend the ^9[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] to suit the regional and local climatic conditions;`
  line
  line `(r) direct every owner or occupier of the building or building complex, being a designated consumer to comply with the provisions of ^9[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] for efficient use of energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(s) direct, any designated consumer referred to in clause (r), if considered necessary, for efficient`
  line `use of energy and its conservation in his building to get energy audit conducted in respect of such`
  line `building by an accredited energy auditor in such manner and intervals of time as may be specified by`
  line regulations;
  line
  line `(t) take all measures necessary to create awareness and disseminate information for efficient use`
  line `of energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(u) arrange and organise training of personnel and specialists in the techniques for efficient use of`
  line `energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(v) take steps to encourage preferential treatment for use of energy efficient equipment or`
  line `appliances:`
  line
  line `^10 [(w) specify the carbon credit trading scheme;`
  line
  line `(x) specify minimum share of consumption of non-fossil sources by designated consumers as energy or feedstock, provided different share of consumption may be specified for different types of non-fossil sources for different designated consumers;]`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers under clauses (p) to (s) shall be exercised in consultation with the concerned State.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 6, for “appliance” (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 6, for “any user or class of users of energy as a designated consumer” (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 6, (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “energy manager” (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 6, for “energy managers” (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “such form and manner” (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 6, for “energy conservation building codes” (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (24754)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 16
  title `Issuance of energy savings certificate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24754&sectionno=14A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Power of Central Government to ^1`
  line `[Issuance of energy savings certificate].--(1) The`
  line `Central Government ^3[ or any agency authorised by it] may issue the energy savings certificate to the`
  line `designated consumer whose energy consumption is less than the prescribed norms and standards in`
  line `accordance with the procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The designated consumer whose energy consumption is more than the prescribed norms and`
  line `standards shall be entitled to purchase the energy savings certificate to comply with the prescribed norms and standards.`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that any other person may also purchase energy saving certificate or carbon credit certificate on voluntary basis.] ]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 7, (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. Act 19 of 2022, s. 7, for the marginal heading "issue energy savings certificate" (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_aa:
  sectionId (72537)
  sectionNo 14AA
  orderNo 17
  title `Issuance of carbon credit certificate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=72537&sectionno=14AA&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_14_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[14AA. Issuance of carbon credit certificate.—(1) The Central Government, or any agency`
  line `authorised by it may issue carbon credit certificate to the registered entity which complies with the`
  line `requirements of the carbon credit trading scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) The registered entity shall be entitled to purchase or sell the carbon credit certificate in accordance`
  line `with carbon credit trading scheme specified under clause (w) of section 14.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_b:
  sectionId (24755)
  sectionNo 14B
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Central Government to specify value of energy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24755&sectionno=14B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[14B. Power of Central Government to specify value of energy.--The Central Government may, in`
  line `consultation with the Bureau, prescribe the value of per metric ton of oil equivalent of energy consumed`
  line `for the purposes of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24756)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of State Government to enforce certain provisions for efficient use of energy and its conservation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24756&sectionno=15&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, in consultation with the Bureau--`
  line
  line `(a) amend the ^1[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] to suit the regional and local`
  line `climatic conditions and may, by rules made by it, specify and notify ^1`
  line `[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] with respect to use of energy in the buildings ^2 [and implement the same`
  line `through building bye-laws of the State];`
  line
  line `(b) direct every owner or occupier of a building or building complex being a designated consumer`
  line `to comply with the provisions of the ^1[energy conservation and sustainable building codes];`
  line
  line `(c) direct, if considered necessary for efficient use of energy and its conservation, any designated`
  line `consumer referred to in clause (b) to get energy audit conducted by an accredited energy auditor in`
  line `such manner and at such intervals of time as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(d) designate any agency as designated agency to coordinate, regulate and enforce provisions of`
  line `this Act within the State;`
  line
  line `(e) take all measures necessary to create awareness and disseminate information for efficient use`
  line `of energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(f) arrange and organise training of personnel and specialists in the techniques for efficient use of`
  line `energy and its conservation;`
  line
  line `(g) take steps to encourage preferential treatment for use of energy efficient equipment or`
  line appliances;
  line
  line `(h) direct, any designated consumer to furnish to the designated agency, in such form and manner`
  line `and within such period as may be specified by rules made by it, information with regard to the energy`
  line `consumed by such consumer;`
  line
  line `^3[(ha) levy such fee as may be prescribed for the services rendered by the designated agency to`
  line `promote efficient use of energy and its conservation under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(i) specify the matters to be included for the purposes of inspection under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 9, for “energy conservation building codes” (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (72538)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 20
  title `Budget of designated agency.`
  content `^1[15A. Budget of designated agency.—The designated agency shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure and forward the same to the State Government, which shall include the same in the annual budget.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=72538&sectionno=15A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24757)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title `Establishment of Fund by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 11, for section 16 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24757&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1]16. Establishment of Fund by State Government.--(1) There shall be constituted a Fund for the purposes of promotion of efficient use of energy and its conservation within the State to be called the State Energy Conservation Fund and there shall be credited thereto--.`
  line
  line `(a) all grants and loans that may be made by the State Government or the Central Government or any other organisation or individual for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees received by the State Government or the designated agency under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by the State Government or the designated agency from such other sources as may be decided by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be utilised for meeting the expenses--`
  line
  line `(a) of the designated agency in the discharge of its functions;`
  line
  line `(b) for the objects and purposes authorised by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Fund created under sub-section (1) shall be administered by such person or authority and in such manner as may be prescribed by the rules made by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24758)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24758&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The designated agency may appoint, after the expiry of five years`
  line `from the date of commencement of this Act, as many inspecting officers as may be necessary for the`
  line `purpose of ensuring compliance with energy consumption standards specified under clause (a) of`
  line `section 14 or ensure display of particulars on label on equipment or appliance specified under clause (b)`
  line `of section 14 or for the purpose of performing such other functions as may be assigned to them.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules made under this Act, an inspecting officer shall have power to--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect any operation carried on or in connection with the equipment or appliance specified`
  line `under clause (b) of section 14 or in respect of which energy standards under clause (a) of section 14`
  line `have been specified;`
  line
  line `(b) enter any place of designated consumer at which the energy is used for any activity and may`
  line `require any proprietor, employee, director, manager or secretary or any other person who may be`
  line `attending in any manner to or helping in, carrying on any activity with the help of energy--`
  line
  line `(i) to afford him necessary facility to inspect--`
  line
  line `(A) any equipment or appliance as he may require and which may be available at such`
  line place;
  line
  line `(B) any production process to ascertain the energy consumption norms and standards;`
  line
  line `(ii) to make an inventory of stock of any equipment or appliance checked or verified by him;`
  line
  line `(iii) to record the statement of any person which may be useful for, or relevant to, for efficient`
  line `use of energy and its conservation under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) An inspecting officer may enter any place of designated consumer--`
  line
  line `(a) where any activity with the help of energy is carried on; and`
  line
  line `(b) where any equipment or appliance notified under clause (b) of section 14 has been kept,`
  line
  line `during the hours at which such place is open for production or conduct of business connected therewith.`
  line
  line `(4) An inspecting officer acting under this section shall, on no account, remove or cause to be`
  line `removed from the place wherein he has entered, any equipment or appliance or books of account or other`
  line documents.
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24759)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Central Government or State Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24759&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government or the State Government may, in the exercise of its powers and performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act and for efficient use of energy and its conservation, issue such directions in writing as it`
  line `deems fit for the purposes of this Act to any person, officer, authority or any designated consumer and`
  line `such person, officer or authority or any designated consumer shall be bound to comply with such`
  line directions.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section includes the power to direct--`
  line
  line `(a) regulation of norms for process and energy consumption standards in any industry or building`
  line `or building complex; or`
  line
  line `(b) regulation of the energy consumption standards for equipment and appliances.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24760)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title `Grants and loans by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24760&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Bureau or to the State Governments`
  line `grants and loans of such sums of money as the Central Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24761)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Establishment of Fund by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24761&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be`
  line `called as the Central Energy Conservation Fund and there shall be credited thereto--`
  line
  line `(a) any grants and loans made to the Bureau by the Central Government under section 19;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees received by the Bureau under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by the Bureau from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salary, allowances and other remuneration of Director-General, Secretary, officers and`
  line `other employees of the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(b) expenses of the Bureau in the discharge of its functions under section 13;`
  line
  line `(c) fee and allowances to be paid to the members of the Governing Council under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24762)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Borrowing powers of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24762&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau may, with the consent of the Central`
  line `Government or in accordance with the terms of any general or special authority given to it by the Central`
  line `Government, borrow money from any source as it may deem fit for discharging all or any of its functions`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may guarantee, in such manner as it thinks fit, the repayment of the`
  line `principal and the payment of interest thereon with respect to the loans borrowed by the Bureau under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24763)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24763&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Bureau shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may`
  line `be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the`
  line `Bureau and forward the same to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24764)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24764&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Bureau shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year`
  line `as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous financial`
  line `year, and submit a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24765)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 29
  title `Annual report to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24765&sectionno=24&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall cause the annual`
  line `report referred to in section 23 to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of`
  line Parliament.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24766)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24766&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Bureau shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Bureau to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Bureau shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts, and in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Bureau as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24767)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 31
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24767&sectionno=26&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person fails to comply with the provisions of clause (c) or clause (d) or`
  line `clause (h) or clause (i) or clause (k) or clause (l) ^1*** or clause (r) or clause (s) of section 14 or clause (b)`
  line `or clause (c) or clause (h) of section 15, he shall be liable to a penalty which shall not exceed ^2[ten lakh`
  line `rupees] for each such failure and, in the case of continuing failure, with an additional penalty which may`
  line `extend to ^3[ten thousand rupees] for every day during which such failure continues:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be liable to pay penalty within five years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) If any person fails to comply with the provisions of clause (n) of section 14, he shall be liable`
  line `to a penalty which shall not exceed ten lakh rupees and, in the case of continuing failure, with an`
  line `additional penalty which shall not be less than the price of every metric ton of oil equivalent of energy,`
  line `prescribed under this Act, that is in excess of the prescribed norms.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount payable under this section, if not paid, may be recovered as if it were an arrear of`
  line `land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words, brackets and letter "or clause (n)" omitted by Act of 28 of 2010, s. 8 (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "ten thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (24768)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24768&sectionno=27&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of adjudging under section 26, the State Commission`
  line `shall appoint any of its members to be an adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government, after giving any person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard for the purpose of imposing any penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding an inquiry, the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or`
  line `produce any document which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry, and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has failed to`
  line `comply with the provisions of any of the clauses of the sections specified in section 26, he may impose`
  line `such penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of any of those clauses of that section:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a State Commission has not been established in a State, the Government of that`
  line `State shall appoint any of its officer not below the rank equivalent to a Secretary dealing with legal affairs`
  line `in that State to be an adjudicating officer for the purposes of this section and such officer shall cease to be`
  line `an adjudicating officer immediately on the appointment of an adjudicating officer by the State`
  line `Commission on its establishment in that State:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an adjudicating officer appointed by a State Government ceased to be an`
  line `adjudicating officer, he shall transfer to the adjudicating officer appointed by the State Commission all`
  line `matters being adjudicated by him and thereafter the adjudicating officer appointed by the State`
  line `Commission shall adjudicate the penalties on such matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (72539)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of State Commission to make regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=72539&sectionno=27A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line ^1[
  line `27A. Power of State Commission to make regulations.--(1) The State Commission may, by`
  line `notification, make regulations for discharging its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of making application before the State Commission and the fee payable;`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter which is to be, or may be, provided by regulations by the State Commission`
  line `for the purposes of its function:`
  line
  line `Provided that every regulation made by the State Commission under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature consists of one House, before that House.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (24769)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 34
  title `Factors to be taken into account by adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24769&sectionno=28&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `While adjudicating the quantum of`
  line `penalty under section 26, the adjudicating officer shall have due regard to the following factors,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of disproportionate gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a`
  line `result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the repetitive nature of the default.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(c) the loss caused to a consumer and amount of compensation thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (24770)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 35
  title `Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24770&sectionno=29&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit`
  line `or proceeding in respect of any matter which an adjudicating officer appointed under this Act or the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal is empowered by or under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by`
  line `any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power`
  line `conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (24771)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 36
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 9, for section 30 (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24771&sectionno=30&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Appellate Tribunal.--The Appellate Tribunal established under section 110 of the Electricity`
  line `Act, 2003 (36 of 2003) shall, without prejudice to the provisions of the Electricity Act, 2003, be the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal for the purposes of this Act and hear appeals against the orders of the adjudicating`
  line `officer or the Central Government or the State Government or any other authority under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (24772)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 37
  title `Appeal to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24772&sectionno=31&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved, by an order made by an adjudicating`
  line `officer or the Central Government or the State Government or any other authority under this Act, may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal for Energy Conservation:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person, appealing against the order of the adjudicating officer levying any penalty,`
  line `shall, while filing the appeal, deposit the amount of such penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where in any particular case, the Appellate Tribunal is of the opinion that the`
  line `deposit of such penalty would cause undue hardship to such person, the Appellate Tribunal may dispense`
  line `with such deposit subject to such conditions as it may deem fit to impose so as to safeguard the realisation`
  line `of penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the order made by the adjudicating officer or the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or any other authority is received by the aggrieved person and it shall be in such form,`
  line `verified in such manner and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties`
  line `to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal and`
  line `to the concerned adjudicating officer or the Central Government or the State Government or any other`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(5) The appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with by it as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within one`
  line `hundred and eighty days from the date of receipt of the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an appeal could not be disposed of within the said period of one hundred and`
  line `eighty days, the Appellate Tribunal shall record its reasons in writing for not disposing of the appeal`
  line `within the said period.`
  line
  line `(6) The Appellate Tribunal may, for the purpose of examining the legality, propriety or correctness of`
  line `any order made by the adjudicating officer or the Central Government or the State Government or any`
  line `other authority under this Act, as the case may be, in relation to any proceeding, on its own motion or`
  line `otherwise, call for the records of such proceedings and make such order in the case as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (24773)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 38
  title `Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 10 (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24773&sectionno=31A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^11[31A. Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.--The provisions of sections 120 to 123 (both`
  line `inclusive) of the Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003) shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal in the discharge of its functions under this Act as they apply to it in the discharge of its function`
  line `under the Electricity Act, 2003.]`
