obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (24786)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 51
  title `Right of appellant to take assistance of legal practitioner or accredited auditor and of Government to appoint presenting officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24786&sectionno=44&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person preferring an appeal to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under this Act may either appear in person or take the assistance of a legal practitioner or an`
  line `accredited energy auditor of his choice to present his case before the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may`
  line be.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the State Government may authorise one or more legal practitioners`
  line `or any of its officers to act as presenting officers and every person so authorised may present the case`
  line `with respect to any appeal before the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (24787)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 52
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24787&sectionno=45&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, may, file an appeal to the Supreme Court within sixty days from the date of communication of the decision or order of the Appellate Tribunal to him, on any one or more of the grounds specified in`
  line `section 100 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (24788)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24788&sectionno=46&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Act, the Bureau shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its`
  line `functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government`
  line `may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Bureau shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (24789)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 54
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24789&sectionno=47&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of grave emergency, the Bureau is unable to discharge the functions and`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Bureau has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default, the financial position of the Bureau`
  line `had deteriorated or the administration of the Bureau had deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, supersede the Bureau for such period, not exceeding six months, as`
  line `may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Bureau,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members referred to in clauses (o), (p) and (q) of sub-section (2) of section 4 shall, as`
  line `from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Bureau, shall until the Bureau is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central Government`
  line `may direct; and`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Bureau shall, until the Bureau is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may reconstitute the Bureau by a fresh appointment and in such`
  line `case any person or persons who vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2), shall not be`
  line `deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time, before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, take action under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (24790)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 55
  title `Default by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24790&sectionno=48&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a company makes a default in complying with the provisions`
  line `of clause (c) or clause (d) or clause (h) or clause (i) or clause (k) or clause (l) or clause (n) or clause (r) or`
  line `clause (s) of section 14 or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (h) of section 15, every person who at the time`
  line `of such contravention was in charge of, and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the`
  line `business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to have acted in contravention of the said provisions and shall be liable to be proceeded against and imposed penalty under section 26`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable for penalty`
  line `provided in this Act if he proves that the contravention of the aforesaid provisions was committed without`
  line `his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the contravention of the aforesaid`
  line provision.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any contravention of the provisions`
  line `of clause (c) or clause (d) or clause (h) or clause (i) or clause (k) or clause (l) or clause (n) or clause (r) or`
  line `clause (s) of section 14 or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (h) of section 15 has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to`
  line `have contravened the said provisions and shall be liable to be proceeded for imposition of penalty`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "company" means a body corporate and includes a`
  line `firm or other association of individuals.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (24791)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 56
  title `Exemption from tax on income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24791&sectionno=49&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act,`
  line `1961 (43 of 1961) or any other enactment for the time being in force relating to tax on income, profits or`
  line gains--
  line
  line `(a) the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(b) the existing Energy Management Centre from the date of its constitution to the date of`
  line `establishment of the Bureau,`
  line
  line `shall not be liable to pay any income-tax or any tax in respect of their income, profits or gains derived.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (24792)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 57
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24792&sectionno=50&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or Director-General or Secretary or State Government or any officer`
  line `of those Governments or State Commission or its members or any member or officer or other employee`
  line `of the Bureau for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules`
  line `or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (24793)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 58
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24793&sectionno=51&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The Bureau may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any member,`
  line `member of the committee, officer of the Bureau or any other person subject to such conditions, if any, as`
  line `may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act (except the powers under`
  line `section 58) as it may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (24794)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24794&sectionno=52&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Every designated consumer or manufacturer of equipment or`
  line `appliance ^1`
  line `[or any other person or entity covered under this Act shall furnish to the Bureau such`
  line `information, documents or records relating to energy consumption, and such samples] of any material or`
  line `substance used in relation to any equipment or appliance, as the Bureau may require`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 15, for the words, brackets, letter and figures "specified under clause (b) of section 14 shall supply`
  line `the Bureau with such information, and with such samples" (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (24795)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24795&sectionno=53&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government or the State Government is of the opinion that it is`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, it may, by notification and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified in the notification, exempt any designated consumer or class of designated`
  line `consumers from application of all or any of the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall not grant`
  line `exemption to any designated consumer or class of designated consumers for a period exceeding five`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall`
  line `consult the Bureau of Energy Efficiency before granting such exemption.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (24796)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 61
  title `Chairperson, Members, officers and employees of the Appellate Tribunal, Members of State Commission, Director-General, Secretary, members, officers and employees of the Bureau to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by Act of 28 of 2010, s. 12 (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24796&sectionno=54&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `The ^1*** members, Director-General, Secretary, officers and other employees of the`
  line `Bureau shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (24797)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24797&sectionno=55&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give`
  line `directions to a State Government or the Bureau as to carrying out into execution of this Act in the State.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (24798)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 63
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24798&sectionno=56&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) such number of persons to be appointed as members by the Central Government under clauses`
  line `(o), (p) and (q) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the fee and allowances to be paid to the members under sub-section (5) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the salary and allowances payable to the Director-General and other terms and conditions of`
  line `his service and other terms and conditions of service of the Secretary of the Bureau under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the terms and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Bureau under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) performing such other functions by the Bureau, as may be prescribed, under clause (u) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(f) the energy consumption norms and standards for designated consumers under clause (g) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribing the different norms and standards for different designated consumers under the`
  line `proviso to clause (g) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(h) the form and manner and the time within which information with regard to energy consumed`
  line `and the action taken on the recommendations of the accredited energy auditor be furnished under`
  line `clause (k) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner in which the status of energy consumption be submitted under clause (i)`
  line `of section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) the minimum qualifications for ^1[energy auditors and energy managers] under clause (m) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and manner for preparation of scheme and its implementation under clause (o) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(l) the ^2[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] under clause (p) of section 14;;`
  line
  line `^3[(la) prescribing the procedure for issuing the energy savings certificate under sub-section (1) of section 14A;`
  line
  line `(laa) the value of per metric ton of oil equivalent of energy consumed under section 14B;]`
  line
  line `(m) the matters relating to inspection under sub-section (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(n) the form in which, and the time at which, the Bureau shall prepare its budget under section 22;`
  line
  line `(o) the form in which, and the time at which, the Bureau shall prepare its annual report under`
  line `section 23;`
  line
  line `(p) the form in which the accounts of the Bureau shall be maintained under section 25;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of holding inquiry under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(r) the form and fee for filing appeal under sub-section (2) of section 31;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(v) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, or may be made, by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 13, for "energy managers" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 16, for "energy conservation building codes" (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 13, (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `4. Cls. (s), (t) and (u) omitted by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (24799)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24799&sectionno=57&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act and not inconsistent with the rules, if any, made by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) ^1[energy conservation and sustainable building codes] under clause (a) of section 15;`
  line ;
  line
  line `(b) the form, the manner and the period within which information with regard to energy`
  line `consumption shall be furnished under clause (h) of section 15;`
  line
  line `^2[(ba) the fee to be levied for the services rendered by the designated agency for promoting`
  line `efficient use of energy and its conservation under clause (ha) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(bb) the form in which and the time at which, the budget of the designated agency shall be`
  line `prepared under section 15A;]`
  line
  line `(c) the person or any authority who shall administer the Fund and the manner in which the Fund`
  line `shall be administered under sub-^3[section (3)] of section 16;`
  line
  line `(d) the matters to be included for the purposes of inspection under sub-section (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be made, or may be made, by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2023, s. 17, for "energy conservation building codes" (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 17, ibid.., for “section (4)” (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (24800)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 65
  title `Power of Bureau to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24800&sectionno=58&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government and subject to the condition of previous publication, by notification, make`
  line `regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places of the meetings of the Governing Council and the procedure to be`
  line `followed at such meetings under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the members of advisory committees constituted under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and duties that may be exercised and discharged by the Director-General of the`
  line `Bureau under sub-section (6) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the levy of fee for services provided for promoting efficient use of energy and its conservation`
  line `under clause (n) of sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(e) the list of accredited energy auditors under clause (o) of sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `^1[(f) the qualifications, criteria and conditions subject to which a person may be accredited as an`
  line `energy auditor and the procedure for such accreditation under clause (p) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 13;]`
  line
  line `(g) the manner and the intervals of time in which the energy audit shall be conducted under clause`
  line `(q) of sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(h) certification procedure for ^2[energy auditors and energy managers] under clause (r) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `^3[(ha) the purposes, and the terms and conditions subject to which, an agency may be authorised`
  line `to carry out the functions of the Bureau under clause (tb) of sub-section (2) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(hb) the technical qualification to test samples under clause (tc) of sub-section (2) of section 13;]`
  line
  line `(i) particulars required to be displayed on label and the manner of their display under clause (d) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner and the intervals of time for conduct of energy audit under clause (h) or clause (s)`
  line `of section 14;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner and the intervals of time for conducting energy audit by an accredited energy`
  line `auditor under clause (c) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2010, s. 14, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "energy managers" (w.e.f. 24-8-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 19 of 2022, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-1-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (24801)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 66
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament and State Legislature.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24801&sectionno=59&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule`
  line `made by the Central Government and every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or regulation, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should`
  line `not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no`
  line `effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the State Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature consists of`
  line `one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (24802)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 67
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24802&sectionno=60&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (24803)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 68
  title `Provisions of Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24803&sectionno=61&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall not apply to`
  line `the Ministry or Department of the Central Government dealing with Defence, Atomic Energy or such`
  line `other similar Ministries or Departments or undertakings or Boards or institutions under the control of such`
  line `Ministries or Departments as may be notified by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (24804)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 69
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452&sectionId=24804&sectionno=62&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_19_22_00003_200152_1517807324452
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `date of the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
